title: Kettlebell Training
author: Steve Cotter
breadCrumbs: Books › Health, Fitness & Dieting › Exercise & Fitness
bookDescription: Kettlebells have been around for hundreds of years but have seen rapid international growth over the last decade. It is no wonder that kettlebells have become so popular across the world: They provide an effective and inexpensive tool for improving mobility; promote fat loss; increase endurance, strength, and power; and enhance sport performance.Kettlebell Training, Second Edition, is an easy-to-use, no-nonsense guide that will get you started on setting goals, assessing your fitness level, and selecting exercises. You’ll learn how to exercise safely and efficiently to maximize results with 69 kettlebell programs—from beginner to advanced—for mobility, fat loss, endurance, strength, power, and sport performance. The nearly 100 exercises are accompanied by step-by-step instructions, detailed photo sequences, and training tips—instantly accessible and perfect for at home or in the gym. Also included are information about common errors and error corrections as well as sport-specific cross-training programs.In the second edition, renowned kettlebell expert and certified strength and conditioning expert Steve Cotter provides insight into the history and value of kettlebell training. He examines the world of kettlebell sport in an interview with kettlebell sport world champion Denis Vasilev and devotes a chapter to kettlebell competition. In addition, the second edition will help you to better understand the lifestyle of kettlebell training, demonstrating how kettlebells fit into overall fitness, health, and well-being.More than exercises, Kettlebell Training contains proven programs that will produce results. Whether you are training for performance, appearance, or general fitness, Kettlebell Training has the exercises, programs, and advice you need for the results you want. It’s a complete guide that you’ll turn to again and again.Earn continuing education credits/units! A continuing education course and exam that uses this book is also available. It may be purchased separately or as part of a package that includes all the course materials and exam.

aPlusContent.title: Product Description
aPlusContent.rawText:
Product Description
One Kettlebell, Serious Results 
Want to build major muscle? Save yourself some cash and skip buying all that expensive gym equipment. With No Gym Required: Kettlebells, you get everything you need for a total-body overhaul without breaking the bank. 
This strategic plan will help you master the fundamentals, like swings and cleans, then conquer complex multi-move flows, and, finally, learn the secret to building your own killer kettlebell workouts. At the end of 30 days, you can build strength, boost your metabolism, blast fat, and increase your overall athleticism. 
Why Kettlebells Work 
It might not look like much, but take it from us: the kettlebell is your ticket to faster fitness. With just one kettlebell (or two or three), you can start pushing toward your workout goals and have a ton of fun while doing it. 
The kettlebell is a unique fitness tool, in part of the style of exercises it lets you do. They’re one of the easiest weights to move around during your workout and are adaptable to your strength and level. One kettlebell in combination with your body weight will help you effectively get major gains, build muscle, and condition your entire body. 
Master the Art of the Kettlebell Flow and Get Shredded All Over 
You can master the art of kettlebell flow in just 30 days! This four-part plan will help you build strength, muscle, and athleticism, all while elevating your heart rate, frying calories, and challenging your coordination. It’s the fun alternative to spending hours in the gym! 
Part 1: Kettlebell Basics 
At the beginning of this ultimate program, you’ll learn how to properly use your kettlebell, discover four rules for getting big gains, dive into seven fundamental kettlebell movements, and set yourself up for success for the duration of your plan. 
Part 2: Your Workout Plans 
Here’s where the fun begins! The experts at Men’s Health will guide you through your 30-day kettlebell journey with four distinct parts: practice sessions, non-flow workouts, 2-move flows, and 3-(or more) move flows. Plus you’ll get 36 extra workouts to help you develop a razor-sharp technique! 
Part 3: The Exercises 
At the end of this plan, you’ll find an exercise glossary filled with upper-body exercises, total-body exercises, core exercises, and ballistic exercises so you can build your own program, plus extra space to write notes and track your progress.

bookDescription: The book *“Kettlebell Exercises”* was originally published in 1928 in Moscow in the then-established Soviet Union.Ivan Lebedev, also known as “Uncle Vanya,” was a prolific author of publications on Physical Culture. It outlines exercises that would later become foundational in any kettlebell training system.You will find, in an orderly and progressive manner, explanations and demonstrations of exercises such as the snatch, jerk, press, clean, "windmill" (seesaw), double lifts, vertical pulls, curls, bottom-up lifts, crucifixes, and the Turkish get-up (TGU).In addition, it contains training routines, a variety of "Special" or "Non-Conventional" Exercises, as well as tips and guidelines for group classes and kettlebell competitions.In these pages, we present the complete original content, translated from the original Russian into Spanish for the first time in history. You will also find notes, personal comments, and opinions by Jerónimo Milo, along with the colorful sections on “Masters of Strength.”WITH THE “KETTLEBELL EXERCISES BY IVAN LEBEDEV” MANUAL, YOU WILL BE ABLE TO:- Learn the traditional kettlebell exercises according to Ivan Lebedev’s school.- Understand the methods, philosophy, and practice guidelines of the original kettlebell system.- Train with kettlebells in the Old School style.- Discover the fascinating stories of the “Masters of Strength.”THE “KETTLEBELL EXERCISES BY IVAN LEBEDEV” MANUAL INCLUDES:- 30 Traditional Kettlebell Exercises.- Basic rules, practical tips, and key points for Kettlebell Training, as used by the Old Russian Strongmen.- Traditional Training Routines for “Strong Beginners” and “Experienced Practitioners.”- 8 biographies of “Masters of Strength,” illustrating and contextualizing Kettlebell Training of the era.- 86 pages – The COMPLETE original text, translated into Spanish for the first time, with fully restored drawings and illustrations.
